From a2b6d482ca7f4b879ee8aa7f5b7f01069d92e778 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: temp <temp@temp.com>
Date: Sat, 4 Jul 2026 18:16:21 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] Implement schedule write for Yooai devices (schedule slot 0)
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Decoded the schedule-write frame from the decompiled app
(com.bumptech.glide.d.h0(), non-Grasse branch — matches this device
family since it uses standard BleUtils.getBytes() framing everywhere
else):

  type=0x14, payload: [enabled(1)] [slot(1)] [weekday_mask LE16]
  [start_min LE16] [stop_min LE16] [run_sec LE16] [pause_sec LE16]
  [timer_id LE32]

weekday_mask bit0..6 = Mon..Sun (confirmed via ModeWeekSetAdapter),
bit7 auto-set when any day selected (mirrors the app). timer_id is a
cloud-assigned field in the real app; using 0 since this device has no
cloud account — untested whether the device validates it.

New entities: 7 weekday switches (Mon-Sun) + Schedule Enabled switch.
Re-enabled Start Time / End Time / Work Duration / Pause Duration,
now wired through the existing generic _write_schedule_to_device()
dispatcher via a new YooaiBleProtocol.build_schedule().
---
